  "prompt": "What are some free alternatives to Aha.io?",
  "response": "There are several free alternatives to Aha.io that you can consider for product management, project planning, and roadmapping. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Trello**: Trello is a popular project management tool that uses boards, lists, and cards to organize tasks and collaborate with team members. It\u2019s user-friendly and has a free tier with essential features.\n\n2. **Asana**: Asana is another robust project management tool that allows teams to track work, manage projects, and collaborate effectively. The free version includes task lists, project timelines, and basic reporting.\n\n3. **Jira**: Jira, developed by Atlassian, is widely used for issue tracking and agile project management. It offers a free tier for small teams, which includes essential features for managing tasks and projects.\n\n4. **ClickUp**: ClickUp is a versatile project management tool that offers a free tier with a range of features, including task management, docs, goals, and integrations with other tools.\n\n5. **Notion**: Notion is an all-in-one workspace that combines note-taking, task management, databases, and collaboration features. The free version is quite powerful and suitable for individuals and small teams.\n\n6. **Wrike**: Wrike is a project management and collaboration tool that offers a free plan with basic features for small teams. It includes task management, file sharing, and collaboration tools.\n\n7. **Monday.com**: Monday.com provides a free tier that allows small teams to manage workflows, projects, and collaboration. It offers customizable boards and integrations with other tools.\n\n8. **Bitrix24**: Bitrix24 is a comprehensive business tool that includes project management, CRM, communication, and collaboration features. It has a free plan with a generous set of features.\n\nEach of these tools has its strengths and unique features, so the best choice depends on your specific needs and preferences.",
